text: Roman Alexandrovich Golovchenko (, Russian: Роман Александрович Головченко; born 10 August 1973) is a Belarusian politician. He has been the Prime Minister of Belarus since 4 June 2020. In June 2022, Golovchenko was blacklisted by Canada. On March 10, 2025, he was no longer Prime Minister and became Chairman of the Board of the National Bank of Belarus. ==References== Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:Prime ministers of Belarus
